&lt;h1&gt;Practice&lt;strong&gt; Manager &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Hours: 37.5 a week&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Salary: 50 - 60K dependent on experience&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Modality Partnership Mid-Sussex Division&lt;/strong&gt; are looking for a dual site Practice Manager to join their &lt;strong&gt;Judges Close Surgery &amp; Ship Street Surgery s&lt;/strong&gt;ites in East Grinstead.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Modality Mid-Sussex Division comprises  of four local practices Crawley Down Health Centre, Park View Health Partnership alongside Judges Close &amp; Ship Street Surgery (40 practices nationally as part of the Modality Super-Partnership.)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This brings huge benefits and scope for innovation and development with our direction driven nationally by an Executive Board, a robust National Governance structure, rapidly emerging IT offerings such as eConsult and PushDr and opportunities for research. Despite this, we still believe strongly in maintaining friendly practice focused sites&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Due to retirement we are seeking an experienced Practice Manager looking to develop their career. Strong HR skills are sought as part of your role will be to lead on HR matters across the division.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Covid -19 has been a huge catalyst for change in primary care. We are currently in the process of a clinical redesign to reflect this, and we continue to develop ways of benefitting from the scale of having a Division with over 30,000 patients.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt; Judges Close and Ship Street surgeries are just a few minutes walk apart and are based right in the centre of East Grinstead, a traditional market town with a 14th century High Street bustling with shops, restaurants and Cafes.We are surrounded by beautiful Sussex countryside and are midway between London and Brighton.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Both practices have a long tradition of teaching GP trainees and medical students from Brighton and Sussex Medical School. We work alongside allied professionals at both sites including pharmacists, paramedics and nurse practitioners. &lt;br /&gt; &lt;br /&gt; For further information or to arrange informal visit please contact Dr. Sharon Pruden, GP Partner.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;           Closing date for applications:23.11.2020&lt;/p&gt;
